message: If you want political advertising Martin, please pay for it like anyone else. Don't use wikipedia.
This article is a disgrace to Wikipedia. It provides free advertising for a weblog dedicated to inciting hatred against muslims. Either a) Make it objective or b) Delete it.
Contributors to Harrys Place are using wikipedia for free advertising. They do not accept edits by others.
Humanitarian intervention is a term invented to give traditional imperialist interventions a "progressive" gloss. It should not be used without qualification.
Mezigue is using wikipedia as free advertising for a political blog. Unacceptable.

Calling a spade a spade.
Harrys Place was not a frequent subject of Norman Johnson's column. www.grauniad.org does not exist. These insertions were merely self-serving.

Removed dead link. However, not even sure that all this discussion about HP's on-off relationship with The Guardian is worthy of inclusion on wikipedia.
Sorry but I know for a fact that the comments pages are NOT open. Contributors with dissident views are banned.
Same comment as before. It is entirely a matter of Harry's Place opinion that the left is totalitarian and pro-Islamist. Original text treated opinion as fact.
Again, unacceptable point of view content. Harrys Place might consider the left "antisemitic" but others are not of the same opinion.
Removed highly speculative information about an anonymous contributor. If the contributor wants to remain anonymous up to him, but it makes the info unverifiable.
Introduced more objective language. The article should not take HP contributors' motivational claims at face value..
Removed point of view comment on Dave Dudley feature: "humour-less far left and its lack of self-awareness". Statements like this need substantiation on wikipedia.
Have added an external link relating to the polemic with anti-zionist Jews, at Matty's request.
Response to Matty's Undoing of several hours of work.
I discussed my changes and they were reviewed by a moderator before I made them. My edits contained a whole host of citations.
Added the word "prominent" to describe the Jews that Harrys Place picks on.
Re addition of paragraph about Harrys Place's attacks on prominent artistic and intellectual Jews.
Added reference to Harrys Place attack on the Jewish academic, Schlomo Sand
Added reference to one of many articles at Harrys Place attacking one of the world's most respected academics, the Jew Noam Chomsky
Addition of reference to one of many articles at Harrys Place attacking the respected Jewish academic, Norman Finkelstein.
Addition of reference to article attacking the comedian of Lithuanian-Jewish descent, Alexei Sayle
Addition of reference to article attacking the Jewish jazz musician, Gilad Atzmon
Addition of paragraph listing some of the Jewish artists and intellectuals attacked by Harrys Place.
I have corrected the title of the linked article to "Pro-War Left"
POV pushing by Mezigue. A wiki page should not simply endorse a political blog that many find offensive, islamophobic, and vindictive towards anti-Zionist Jews.
Use of wikipedia as advertising space is unacceptable.
Have toned down in light of the protest. Have replaced "Most of the articles are insulting towards individual Muslims" to "Many of the articles are insulting towards individual Muslims".
